message: >
  If you reference this work in research, regulatory filings, or professional
  publications, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: software
title: "RGDS: Regulated Gate Decision Support — Decision-Centric AI Governance in Biopharma/Biotech Development"
abstract: >
  An independent ten-question study on the design, implementation, and regulatory
  implications of schema-validated decision logs in phase-gated biopharma/biotech
  development. The RGDS framework addresses the reconstructability crisis that
  drives 25–30% of FDA Complete Response Letters by treating decisions—not
  documents—as the primary governance artifact. The study covers decision
  reconstructability, AI accountability under FDA's January 2025 draft guidance,
  integration overhead, FDA deficiency prevention, decision velocity, ROI modeling,
  implementation phasing, AI governance disclosure, and regulatory mandate trajectory.
